		<tr align="left" valign="top">
			<td class="BoardRowA">
			Anon24.4.255.x&nbsp;			
			</td>
			<td class="BoardRowA">6/7 11:51am</td>
			<td class="BoardRowA"><a name="5820253"><span style="font-weight: bold;">
				Soul Mate
			</span></a></td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				Soulmate <br>   <br> Gamthor, Cleric of Erollisi Marr <br>   <br>  <br> Sit, sit and rest a while my friends for I've a tale that even I can not believe at times. <br>   <br> Long ago I was a Rogue, a Cad, a Pirate, a Bandit, a dock crawler who would prey on the weak and  <br> helpless with no regard for their life.  Many a bar fight have I been in both giving and taking <br> blood.  I have slept with Shadow Knights, Ogres and Trolls ... to just name a few.  My life was <br> meaningless and I intended to end it. <br>   <br> You look at me with your eyes wide and stare at my many scars and eye-patch and wonder how I have <br> now come to this, a simple cleric roaming the areas.  It is simple my friend, she told me to.   <br>   <br> Who you ask? that I can not answer...   <br>   <br> I was in Halas one day, drinking and chasing the wrong type <br> of women when the biggest barbarian I've ever seen entered the bar.  He was refined in the purest <br> furs to come out of Everfrost and I had to have them for my journey and the gold it would fetch <br> on the open market.  I struck up a friendly conversation with this giant and began to ply him  <br> with many pints of ale.  My plan was to get him drunk and just &quot;borrow&quot; his furs, and I skillfully did just that. <br>   <br> I left the area in all haste giddy with glee at my new found fortune.  I escaped to Everfrost where <br> I built a cozy fire and settled in for the night, with my ales to keep me company.  Drunk was <br> I dreaming of the riches I would soon have, and to squander in the establishments that catered <br> to my kind.  I must have dozed off for the next thing I knew I was floating in the air, with the <br> help of the barbarian I robbed, whose hand was firmly grasped around my neck.  I kicked and squirmed <br> trying to escape but to no avail.  I could see the fire in his eyes and knew then that my life <br> would end shortly, and did not care.  He shook me like a rag doll and the world started to fade away into blackness. <br> The last thing I recalled was my body being slammed into a hole in the river where the coldness quickly <br> enveloped me. <br>   <br> I do not recall ever waking up! I opened my eye and I was in a mist, a fog you may say, and I was  <br> cold.  No, not cold but frozen.  It seems I was entombed in a block of ice, cast along the shore of  <br> the river.  It is then that I first saw her. <br>   <br> It looked to me then that she was tending a small fire, but my vision was blurred trying to see  <br> through the ice that surrounded me.  I must have made a sound for she quickly turned toward me  <br> and said &quot;I have finally found you my love, but you disappoint me&quot;.  I have never seen this woman  <br> before, and actually still have not. <br>   <br> She continued on to say &quot;For many seasons I have searched the lands for you, for I have seen you  <br> many times in my dreams&quot;.  that she has consulted with many a shaman, wizards,  <br> and dream tellers and all have given her the same answer.  The answer to who was this man in <br> her dreams  was that I was her &quot;Soulmate&quot;, the one who she needed to join with in order obtain the highest <br> levels of joy in a mortal life. <br>   <br> Soulmate, I have heard the term before but only in passing and by starry eyed lovers.  It used to make me  <br> sick to hear such drivel. <br>   <br> I was still entombed in the ice and could not reply but I could feel her love burning through the  <br> ice... and then she bent over my form and kissed me.  The world exploded into a rainbow of colors,  <br> my heart melted, the ice around me started to fall apart and just as quickly she disappeared. <br>   <br> I crawled to my knees and shouted out &quot;Who are you?&quot;, &quot;Where are you going?&quot;, &quot;Do not leave me!&quot;. <br> The only reply was a whisper upon the wind, it was her for I recognized the voice.  She said &quot;I am your  <br> Solute, I must attend to others in the world who are suffering and will continue to do so for the  <br> rest of my life, I must leave you until you can prove that you are worthy of me and that we can  <br> travel together bringing others happiness&quot;.  &quot;Repent your ways my love she cried and hurry for I yearn  <br> to hold you in my arms and soar with ecstasy at your touch, repent..... become worthy.&quot; <br>   <br> So my friends, I am a cleric.  I give all I have to others and only keep that which will sustain life  <br> for myself.  I travel the lands healing and crushing evil where ever I can and I pray that each  <br> action brings me closer to my Soulmate. <br>   <br> I have run across many who have claimed to be my Soulmate but those tales are for another time. <br>  <p>

							

